        <div class="faq-container">
        <h2>FAQs</h2>
        <p>If you don't see an answer to your question(s) below, send an email or call and I'll be happy to respond!</p>

        <h3>Can I bring alcoholic beverages?</h3>
        <p>Yes.</p>

        <h3>Can I bring food?</h3>
        <p>Yes, a table is provided. I also have a tabletop propane grill upon request.</p>

        <h3>Can children come?</h3>
        <p>Yes, however, if they are less than 90 lbs you will need to bring the appropriate child-size life jacket.</p>

        <h3>Can I bring my pet?</h3>
        <p>No pets are allowed. (Except your spouse.)</p>

        <h3>Can I go skiing or tubing?</h3>
        <p>Insurance regulations prohibit water sports activities.</p>

        <h3>Can I bring more than 6 people?</h3>
        <p>No. U.S. Coast Guard regulations prohibit more than 6 people chartered on a non-purpose-built vessel.</p>

        <h3>Can I make more than 1 stop?</h3>
        <p>Absolutely. Just call or email me to discuss where you want to go.</p>

        <h3>Are tobacco products or smoking allowed?</h3>
        <p>
            Chewing tobacco or vape products are fine. Cigarettes, cigars, or marijuana in any form are not allowed. 
            Marijuana in any form is not permitted to be used or in your possession. As we will be in international waters, federal law prohibits it.
        </p>

        <div class="things-to-consider">
            <h2>Things to Consider</h2>
            <p>There is no bathroom onboard (other than off the back of the boat). I do have a portable porta-potti available if requested. Or I can stop in downtown Toledo or Rossford Marina if the need arises.</p>
            <p>It can get chilly on the water so bring pants and a sweatshirt or blanket.</p>
            <h3>Captain Pete trips are all BYOB.</h3>
        </div>
